{
  "texts": [
    "We then evaluate the differences of the wing-band mean fluxes between the Hα spectrum with the smallest I Hα index value and other spectra with larger I Hα index values.",
    "The criterion for recognizing the consistent Hα profiles in the line wings is that the maximum absolute difference of the wing-band mean fluxes is less than 0.022 (see Appendix C.1 for details on determining the criterion).",
    "The stellar sources that do not meet this criterion or have bad pixels in the line-wing bands of their Hα spectra are removed from our sample.",
    "The situation of recognizing consistent Hα profiles in the line center is more complicated than that in the line wings, since the Hα profiles in line center show different characteristics for stellar sources with different activity levels (see Figure 1).",
    "For the stellar sources with lower activity levels, the Hα profiles in line center are simple as demonstrated in Figures 1a and 1b; while for the stellar sources with higher activity levels, the Hα profiles in line center are more complex as demonstrated in Figures 1c and 1d, especially for the objects with Hα central flux approaching continuum (see Figure 1d)."
  ]
}